# Domain — Auth Rules

- Use secure mechanisms: JWT with short expiry, secure cookies, or session store
- **Never** store passwords in plain text; use strong hashing (bcrypt, argon2)
- Validate tokens and sessions on every protected request
- Enforce **authorization** after authentication (roles, permissions, tenant)
- Use HTTPS in production; secure cookie flags (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite)
- Prefer allowlists for redirect URLs and scopes

Keep auth logic in a dedicated module; inject user/tenant context into services.

Do not expose internal user IDs or sensitive claims unnecessarily.
